        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:30AM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 229 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Rolla, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Morton
and southern Stevens Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
